## Rollout safety
- Assume users and CDN edges may serve a mix of old and new assets during deployment.
- Ensure `index.html` and entry chunk references update atomically with the deployment strategy (avoid orphan chunk references).
- New UI versions should tolerate the backend during rolling deployment when the API contract allows it.

## API and schema coordination
- Avoid coupling a UI release to a backend-only change that is unsafe until all clients update, unless rollout is controlled.
- Prefer additive API changes first; deprecate and remove only after adoption windows when possible.

## Caching and PWA considerations
- If service workers or aggressive caching are used, version caches explicitly and test upgrade paths.
- Do not cache authenticated API responses in shared caches unless explicitly designed for it.

## Operational hygiene
- Feature flags should default safely; document kill switches for risky UI changes.
- Monitor client errors and web vitals after deploy; roll forward or revert with a clear playbook.
